🗑️📡 Garbage Level Monitoring System

📌 Problem Statement:
Unmonitored garbage bins often overflow, causing serious health and
hygiene issues in urban areas. 🏙️🤢 Manual collection schedules are inefficient
and lead to wasted resources.

🎯 Objective:
Develop an IoT-powered system that monitors garbage bin fill levels in real-time
using an ultrasonic sensor and sends instant alerts when the bin is full! 📊🔔

🛠️ Hardware & Software Requirements:
• 📶 NodeMCU or ESP32 (Wi-Fi enabled microcontroller)
• 📏 Ultrasonic Sensor (HC-SR04) for distance/level measurement
• 🔌 Jumper wires, breadboard
• 🔋 Battery pack
• 📱 IoT Dashboard (Blynk / ThingSpeak) for real-time monitoring

🔬 How It Works:
1️⃣ The ultrasonic sensor measures the distance to the garbage surface
2️⃣ As the bin fills up, the distance decreases 📉
3️⃣ Data is sent wirelessly to the cloud dashboard via Wi-Fi 🌐
4️⃣ When the bin reaches a threshold ⚠️, an alert is triggered to municipal teams

🏆 Expected Outcome:
A real-time smart waste management prototype that alerts municipal teams
to clean full bins — improving urban cleanliness 🌿, optimizing collection routes,
and promoting a healthier city environment! 🏙️✨

